:11:\"autoptimize\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:7:\"lang:en\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:11:\"performance\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:4;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"wordpress\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:5;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:3:\"cf7\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:6;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:14:\"contact form 7\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:7;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:27:\"contact form 7 alternatives\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"https://blog.futtta.be/?p=11261\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:338:\"Given the major change in Contact Form 7&#8216;s frontend JavaScript and the problems having to optimize the JS or cache the page after the update, the question I get asked frequently is what alternatives there are to CF7. So here is a very quick rundown of 3 such alternatives: Gravity Forms: premium-only, visual form builder, [&#8230;]\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:5:\"frank\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:3205:\"<p><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/support/plugin/contact-form-7/reviews/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignright wp-image-11264 size-thumbnail\" style=\"border-radius: 50%; object-fit: cover;\" src=\"http://blog.futtta.be/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/cf7_problems-150x150.jpg\" alt=\"Contact Form 7: trouble right here in volcano city!\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" srcset=\"http://blog.futtta.be/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/cf7_problems-150x150.jpg 150w, http://blog.futtta.be/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/cf7_problems.jpg 248w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 150px) 100vw, 150px\" /></a>Given <a href=\"https://blog.futtta.be/2021/02/25/contact-form-7-update-breaks-autoptimize-js-optimization-workaround/\">the <strong>major change in Contact Form 7</strong>&#8216;s frontend JavaScript</a> and the <strong>problems having to optimize</strong> the JS or cache the page after the update, the question I get asked frequently is <strong>what alternatives there are to CF7</strong>.</p>\n<p>So here is a very quick rundown of 3 such alternatives:</p>\n<ol>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.gravityforms.com\">Gravity Forms</a>: premium-only, visual form builder, very flexible, big ecosystem (lots of 3rd party plugins &amp; integrations)</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://formidableforms.com/\">Formidable Forms</a>: has a <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/formidable/\">free Light version</a>, drag &amp; drop interface for building forms, very flexible (we currently use this on autoptimize.com), lots of integrations but smaller ecosystem.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.htmlformsplugin.com/\">HTML Forms</a>: <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/html-forms/\">free plugin</a> from the team that also develops &#8220;Koko Analytics&#8221; (which I now use on all my sites) and &#8220;Mailchimp for WordPress&#8221; with <a href=\"https://www.htmlformsplugin.com/premium-features/\">a premium addon for extra features</a>, similar to Contact Form 7, no frills, very light on JS so great for performance.</li>\n</ol>\n<p>My advice; try <strong>HTML Forms</strong> if you have rather standard contactform-like forms and you&#8217;re not looking for something fancy (which CF7 is not either), try <strong>Formidable</strong> if you need drag &amp; drop form building or if you (will) need more flexibility/ integrations.</p>\n<div class=\'yarpp-related-rss\'>\n<p>Possibly related twitterless twaddle:<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://blog.futtta.be/2018/03/13/taking-over-async-javascript-wordpress-plugin/\" rel=\"bookmark\" title=\"Taking over Async JavaScript WordPress plugin\">Taking over Async JavaScript WordPress plugin </a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://blog.futtta.be/2012/11/06/dipping-below-the-magical-1-second-page-load-time/\" rel=\"bookmark\" title=\"Dipping below the magical 1 second page load time\">Dipping below the magical 1 second page load time </a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://blog.futtta.be/2017/08/11/loading-webfonts-just-for-a-title-switch-to-svg-instead/\" rel=\"bookmark\" title=\"Loading webfonts just for a title? Switch to SVG instead.\">Loading webfonts just for a title? Switch to SVG instead. </a></li>\n</ul></p>\n</div>\n<img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/futtta_wordpress/~4/Di5jPMttMUU\" height=\"1\" width=\"1\" alt=\"\"/>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:67:\"https://blog.futtta.be/2021/03/15/contact-form-7-alternatives/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"4\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:42:\"http://rssnamespace.org/feedburner/ext/1.0\";a:1:{s:8:\"origLink\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:62:\"https://blog.futtta.be/2021/03/15/contact-form-7-alternatives/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:4;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:85:\"\n		\n		\n					\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n					\n										\n					\n					\n			\n		\n		\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:6:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:68:\"Contact Form 7 update breaks Autoptimize JS optimization: workaround\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:63:\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/futtta_wordpress/~3/FoNmwNGHNBE/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:111:\"https://blog.futtta.be/2021/02/25/contact-form-7-update-breaks-autoptimize-js-optimization-workaround/#comments\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Thu, 25 Feb 2021 19:37:28 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:5:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:11:\"autoptimize\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"wordpress\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:6:\"broken\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:3:\"bug\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:4;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:14:\"contact form 7\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"https://blog.futtta.be/?p=11245\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:367:\"Due to a recent major change in Contact Form 7&#8217;s frontend JavaScript Autoptimize users might have to add wp-includes/js/dist the comma-separated JS optimization exclusion list (or in some cases even wp-includes/js). It is nice CF7 gets rid of the jQuery dependancy, but I&#8217;m not sure is replacing that with a significant amount of extra WordPress [&#8230;]\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:5:\"frank\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1570:\"<p>Due to <a href=\"https://contactform7.com/2021/02/02/contact-form-7-54-beta/#overhaul-of-frontside-javascript\">a recent major change in Contact Form 7&#8217;s frontend JavaScript</a> Autoptimize users might have to add <code>wp-includes/js/dist</code> the comma-separated JS optimization exclusion list (or in some cases even <code>wp-includes/js</code>).</p>\n<p>It is nice CF7 gets rid of the jQuery dependancy, but I&#8217;m not sure is replacing that with a significant amount of extra WordPress blocks JS-files was such a good idea?</p>\n<p>Update: additionally the change also introduces nonces (random password-like strings as hidden elements in the form) which can spell serious trouble when using page caching plugins.</p>\n<div class=\'yarpp-related-rss\'>\n<p>Possibly related twitterless twaddle:<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://blog.futtta.be/2016/12/07/wordpress-4-7-custom-background-image-bug-workaround/\" rel=\"bookmark\" title=\"WordPress 4.7 custom background image bug &#038; workaround\">WordPress 4.7 custom background image bug &#038; workaround </a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://blog.futtta.be/2018/11/17/warning-divi-purging-autoptimizes-cache/\" rel=\"bookmark\" title=\"Warning: Divi purging Autoptimize&#8217;s cache!\">Warning: Divi purging Autoptimize&#8217;s cache! </a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://blog.futtta.be/2021/03/15/contact-form-7-alternatives/\" rel=\"bookmark\" title=\"Contact Form 7 alternatives\">Contact Form 7 alternatives </a></li>\n</ul></p>\n</div>\n<img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/futtta_wordpress/~4/FoNmwNGHNBE\" height=\"1\" width=\"1\" alt=\"\"/>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:107:\"https://blog.futtta.be/2021/02/25/contact-form-7-update-breaks-autoptimize-js-optimization-workaround/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"6\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:42:\"http://rssnamespace.org/feedburner/ext/1.0\";a:1:{s:8:\"origLink\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:102:\"https://blog.futtta.be/2021/02/25/contact-form-7-update-breaks-autoptimize-js-optimization-workaround/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:5;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:94:\"\n		\n		\n					\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n					\n										\n					\n					\n			\n		\n		\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:6:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:66:\"Autoptimize Image Optimization to be less “lazy” with pictures\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:63:\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/futtta_wordpress/~3/t9KEITpGo_Q/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:104:\"https://blog.futtta.be/2021/02/18/autoptimize-image-optimization-to-be-less-lazy-with-pictures/#comments\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Thu, 18 Feb 2021 18:04:48 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:8:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:11:\"autoptimize\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:7:\"lang:en\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"wordpress\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:4:\"avif\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:4;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:3:\"img\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:5;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:7:\"picture\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:6;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:6:\"source\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:7;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:4:\"webp\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"https://blog.futtta.be/?p=11239\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:399:\"Up until now Autoptimize, when performing image optimization, relies on JS-based lazyloading (with the great lazysizes component) to differentiate between browser that support different image formats (AVIF, WebP and JPEG as fallback). As JS-based Lazyload is going out of fashion though (with native lazyload being supported by more browsers and WordPress having out-of-the-box support for [&#8230;]\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:5:\"frank\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:2896:\"<p>Up until now Autoptimize, when performing image optimization, relies on JS-based lazyloading (with the great lazysizes component) to differentiate between browser that support different image formats (AVIF, WebP and JPEG as fallback).</p>\n<p>As JS-based Lazyload is going out of fashion though (with <a href=\"https://caniuse.com/loading-lazy-attr\">native lazyload being supported by more browsers</a> and WordPress having out-of-the-box support for it too), it is time to start working on &lt;picture&gt; output in Autoptimize to serve &#8220;nextgen image formats&#8221; where different &lt;source&gt; tags offer the AVIF and WebP files and the &lt;img&gt; tag (which includes the  loading=&#8221;lazy&#8221; attribute) with JPEG as fallback.<a href=\"http://blog.futtta.be/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Selection_999161.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignleft size-large wp-image-11240\" src=\"http://blog.futtta.be/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Selection_999161-1024x92.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"625\" height=\"56\" srcset=\"http://blog.futtta.be/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Selection_999161-1024x92.jpg 1024w, http://blog.futtta.be/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Selection_999161-300x27.jpg 300w, http://blog.futtta.be/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Selection_999161-624x56.jpg 624w, http://blog.futtta.be/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Selection_999161.jpg 1349w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 625px) 100vw, 625px\" /></a></p>\n<p>For now that functionality is in a separate &#8220;power-up&#8221;, <a href=\"https://github.com/futtta/ao-picturize/\">available on Github</a>. If you have Image Optimization active in Autoptimize (and you are on <a href=\"https://github.com/futtta/autoptimize\">the Beta version</a>, Autoptimize 2.8.1 is missing a filter which the power-up needs so <a href=\"https://github.com/futtta/autoptimize/archive/beta.zip\">download &amp; install the Beta</a> if not done yet), you can <a href=\"https://github.com/futtta/ao-picturize/archive/main.zip\">download the plugin Github</a> and give it a go. All feedback is welcome!</p>\n<div class=\'yarpp-related-rss\'>\n<p>Possibly related twitterless twaddle:<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://blog.futtta.be/2020/09/15/want-to-test-avif-images-with-autoptimizes-image-optimization/\" rel=\"bookmark\" title=\"Want to test AVIF images with Autoptimize&#8217;s Image Optimization?\">Want to test AVIF images with Autoptimize&#8217;s Image Optimization? </a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://blog.futtta.be/2020/10/09/autoptimize-with-support-for-avif-images/\" rel=\"bookmark\" title=\"Autoptimize with support for AVIF images\">Autoptimize with support for AVIF images </a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://blog.futtta.be/2019/04/22/easter-bunny-special-autoptimize-2-5/\" rel=\"bookmark\" title=\"Easter bunny special: Autoptimize 2.5\">Easter bunny special: Autoptimize 2.5 </a></li>\n</ul></p>\n</div>\n<img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/futtta_wordpress/~4/t9KEITpGo_Q\" height=\"1\" width=\"1\" alt=\"\"/>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:100:\"https://blog.futtta.be/2021/02/18/autoptimize-image-optimization-to-be-less-lazy-with-pictures/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"1\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:42:\"http://rssnamespace.org/feedburner/ext/1.0\";a:1:{s:8:\"origLink\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:95:\"https://blog.futtta.be/2021/02/18/autoptimize-image-optimization-to-be-less-lazy-with-pictures/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:6;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:88:\"\n		\n		\n					\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n					\n										\n					\n					\n			\n		\n		\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:6:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:46:\"Fix for Elementor 3.1 YouTube not LYTE anymore\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:63:\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/futtta_wordpress/~3/e2i7J_SGaGM/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:90:\"https://blog.futtta.be/2021/02/13/fix-for-elementor-3-1-youtube-not-lyte-anymore/#comments\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Sat, 13 Feb 2021 17:28:54 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:6:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:7:\"lang:en\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"wordpress\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:15:\"wp-youtube-lyte\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:12:\"code snippet\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:4;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"elementor\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:5;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:22:\"koen van den wijngaert\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"https://blog.futtta.be/?p=11236\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:342:\"Elementor 3.1 came with &#8220;refactored YouTube source to use YouTube API in Video widget&#8221; which resulted in WP YouTube Lyte not being able to lyten up the YouTubes any more. Below code snippet (consider it beta) hooks into Elementor to fix this regression; Hat tip to Koen for his assistance in digging into Elementor, much [&#8230;]\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:5:\"frank\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:2244:\"<p>Elementor 3.1 came with &#8220;refactored YouTube source to use YouTube API in Video widget&#8221; which <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/support/topic/wp-youtube-lyte-does-not-work-with-the-newest-elementor-3-1-1/\">resulted in WP YouTube Lyte not being able to lyten up the YouTubes any more</a>. Below code snippet (consider it beta) hooks into Elementor to fix this regression;</p>\n<pre class=\"brush: php; title: ; notranslate\">\nadd_filter( \'elementor/frontend/widget/should_render\', function( $should_render, $elementor_element ) {\n	if ( function_exists( \'lyte_preparse\' ) &amp;&amp; \'Elementor\\Widget_Video\' === get_class( $elementor_element ) ) {\n		$pas = get_private_property( $elementor_element , \'parsed_active_settings\');\n		if ( ! empty( $pas[\'youtube_url\'] ) ) {\n			echo lyte_preparse( $pas[\'youtube_url\'] );\n			return false;\n		}\n	}\n\n	return $should_render;\n}, 10, 2 );\n\n// from https://www.lambda-out-loud.com/posts/accessing-private-properties-php/\nfunction get_private_property( object $object, string $property ) {\n    $array = (array) $object;\n    $propertyLength = strlen( $property );\n    foreach ( $array as $key =&gt; $value ) {\n        if ( substr( $key, -$propertyLength ) === $property ) {\n            return $value;\n        }\n    }\n}\n</pre>\n<p>Hat tip to <a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/vdwijngaert/\">Koen</a> for his assistance in digging into Elementor, much appreciated!</p>\n<div class=\'yarpp-related-rss\'>\n<p>Possibly related twitterless twaddle:<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://blog.futtta.be/2010/12/31/coding-for-the-new-year/\" rel=\"bookmark\" title=\"Coding for the New Year\">Coding for the New Year </a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://blog.futtta.be/2013/03/05/how-to-have-normal-youtube-links-handled-by-wp-youtube-lyte/\" rel=\"bookmark\" title=\"How to have normal YouTube-links handled by WP YouTube Lyte\">How to have normal YouTube-links handled by WP YouTube Lyte </a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://blog.futtta.be/2013/08/22/wp-youtube-lyte-mobile-audio-only-degradation/\" rel=\"bookmark\" title=\"WP YouTube Lyte mobile audio-only degradation\">WP YouTube Lyte mobile audio-only degradation </a></li>\n</ul></p>\n</div>\n<img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/futtta_wordpress/~4/e2i7J_SGaGM\" height=\"1\" width=\"1\" alt=\"\"/>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:86:\"https://blog.futtta.be/2021/02/13/fix-for-elementor-3-1-youtube-not-lyte-anymore/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"2\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:42:\"http://rssnamespace.org/feedburner/ext/1.0\";a:1:{s:8:\"origLink\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:81:\"https://blog.futtta.be/2021/02/13/fix-for-elementor-3-1-youtube-not-lyte-anymore/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:7;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:88:\"\n		\n		\n					\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n					\n										\n					\n					\n			\n		\n		\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:6:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:53:\"AO image optimization: transparent .png to avif issue\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:63:\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/futtta_wordpress/~3/OzcZU5FJxgg/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:95:\"https://blog.futtta.be/2021/02/06/ao-image-optimization-transparent-png-to-avif-issue/#comments\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Sat, 06 Feb 2021 08:12:56 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:6:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:11:\"autoptimize\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:7:\"lang:en\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"wordpress\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:4:\"avif\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:4;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:10:\"shortpixel\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:5;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:12:\"transparency\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"https://blog.futtta.be/?p=11233\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:369:\"if “Load WebP or AVIF in supported browsers?” is on, .png files with transparency will loose that transparency in browsers that support AVIF due to a recent technical change in Shortpixel’s AVIF toolchain. Shortpixel is looking at alternative solutions, but until then as a workaround you can either: add .png to Autoptimize’s lazyload exclusion field [&#8230;]\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:5:\"frank\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1493:\"<p>if “Load WebP or AVIF in supported browsers?” is on, <code>.png</code> files with transparency will loose that transparency in browsers that support AVIF due to a recent technical change in Shortpixel’s AVIF toolchain.</p>\n<p>Shortpixel is looking at alternative solutions, but until then as a workaround you can either:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>add <code>.png</code> to Autoptimize’s lazyload exclusion field</li>\n<li>or to use below code snippet to disable AVIF images;</li>\n</ul>\n<p><code>add_filter( \'autoptimize_filter_imgopt_do_avif\', \'__return_false\');</code></p>\n<div class=\'yarpp-related-rss\'>\n<p>Possibly related twitterless twaddle:<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://blog.futtta.be/2020/10/09/autoptimize-with-support-for-avif-images/\" rel=\"bookmark\" title=\"Autoptimize with support for AVIF images\">Autoptimize with support for AVIF images </a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://blog.futtta.be/2018/05/24/autoptimize-2-4-beta-3-includes-image-optimization/\" rel=\"bookmark\" title=\"Autoptimize 2.4 beta 3 includes image optimization!\">Autoptimize 2.4 beta 3 includes image optimization! </a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://blog.futtta.be/2020/09/15/want-to-test-avif-images-with-autoptimizes-image-optimization/\" rel=\"bookmark\" title=\"Want to test AVIF images with Autoptimize&#8217;s Image Optimization?\">Want to test AVIF images with Autoptimize&#8217;s Image Optimization? </a></li>\n</ul></p>\n</div>\n<img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/futtta_wordpress/~4/OzcZU5FJxgg\" height=\"1\" width=\"1\" alt=\"\"/>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:91:\"https://blog.futtta.be/2021/02/06/ao-image-optimization-transparent-png-to-avif-issue/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"1\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:42:\"http://rssnamespace.org/feedburner/ext/1.0\";a:1:{s:8:\"origLink\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:86:\"https://blog.futtta.be/2021/02/06/ao-image-optimization-transparent-png-to-avif-issue/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:8;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:97:\"\n		\n		\n					\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n					\n										\n					\n					\n			\n		\n		\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:6:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:45:\"AO not lazyloading above the fold; the sequel\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:63:\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/futtta_wordpress/~3/Vt7v4icUVRk/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:73:\"https://blog.futtta.be/2020/12/23/ao-not-lazyloading-the-sequel/#comments\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Wed, 23 Dec 2020 19:53:30 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:9:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:11:\"autoptimize\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:7:\"lang:en\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"wordpress\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:12:\"code snippet\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:4;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:14:\"featured image\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:5;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:8:\"lazyload\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:6;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:4:\"logo\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:7;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:12:\"not lazyload\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:8;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:7:\"preload\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"https://blog.futtta.be/?p=11193\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:347:\"So in the ever-continuing saga of learning, testing and fine-tuning your site&#8217;s settings to get the ultimate in performance you might have enjoyed the new Autoptimize filter/ setting not to lazyload the first N images to keep the impact of lazyloading on Largest Contentfull Paint down? Well, now you can take things a step further [&#8230;]\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:5:\"frank\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:2170:\"<p>So in the ever-continuing saga of learning, testing and fine-tuning your site&#8217;s settings to get the ultimate in performance you might have enjoyed <a href=\"https://blog.futtta.be/2020/12/11/about-that-new-autoptimize-autoptimize_filter_imgopt_lazyload_from_nth-filter/\">the new Autoptimize filter/ setting not to lazyload the first N images</a> to keep the impact of lazyloading on Largest Contentfull Paint down?</p>\n<p>Well, now you can take things a step further with below code snippet, which tells Autoptimize not to lazyload the logo and the featured image (hat tip to <a href=\"https://flying-press.com/\">Gijo Varghese of Flying Press</a> for the idea).</p>\n<pre class=\"brush: php; title: ; notranslate\">add_filter(\'autoptimize_filter_imgopt_lazyload_exclude_array\', function( $lazy_excl ){\n	// site logo.\n	$custom_logo_id = get_theme_mod( \'custom_logo\' );\n	$image = wp_get_attachment_image_src( $custom_logo_id , \'full\' );\n	$logo = $image[0];\n	if ( ! empty( $logo ) ) {\n		$lazy_excl[] = $logo;\n	}\n	// featured image.\n	if ( is_single() || is_page() ) {\n		$featured_img = get_the_post_thumbnail_url();\n		if ( ! empty( $featured_img ) ) {\n			$lazy_excl[] = $featured_img;\n		}\n	}\n	return $lazy_excl;\n});</pre>\n<p>This might end up in a future version of Autoptimize, maybe even preloading those images &#8230; :-)</p>\n<div class=\'yarpp-related-rss\'>\n<p>Possibly related twitterless twaddle:<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://blog.futtta.be/2017/02/24/autoptimize-css-defer-switching-to-loadcss-soon/\" rel=\"bookmark\" title=\"Autoptimize CSS defer switching to loadCSS (soon)\">Autoptimize CSS defer switching to loadCSS (soon) </a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://blog.futtta.be/2019/05/24/google-font-display-swap-in-autoptimize/\" rel=\"bookmark\" title=\"Google Font display swap in Autoptimize?\">Google Font display swap in Autoptimize? </a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://blog.futtta.be/2016/07/24/preparing-for-autoptimize-2-0-3-or-2-1-0/\" rel=\"bookmark\" title=\"Preparing (for) Autoptimize 2.0.3 or 2.1.0\">Preparing (for) Autoptimize 2.0.3 or 2.1.0 </a></li>\n</ul></p>\n</div>\n<img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/futtta_wordpress/~4/Vt7v4icUVRk\" height=\"1\" width=\"1\" alt=\"\"/>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:69:\"https://blog.futtta.be/2020/12/23/ao-not-lazyloading-the-sequel/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"1\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:42:\"http://rssnamespace.org/feedburner/ext/1.0\";a:1:{s:8:\"origLink\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:64:\"https://blog.futtta.be/2020/12/23/ao-not-lazyloading-the-sequel/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:9;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:85:\"\n		